<p>I found the following connection testing code in our repository, and it appears to ignore username and password:</p>  <pre><code>public boolean canConnect() {     try {         ActiveMQConnectionFactory connectionFactory = new ActiveMQConnectionFactory(getUserName(), getPassword(), getURI());         Connection connection = connectionFactory.createConnection(getUserName(), getPassword());         connection.start();         connection.close();         return true;     } catch (URISyntaxException | JMSException ex) {         return false;     } } </code></pre>  <p>I can provide ANY username/password combination that I like and it still connects successfully.</p>  <p>When I connect to the admin console via a web browser <code>http://myIPaddress:8161/admin/index.jsp</code> it requires the right password, as specified in the file <code>jetty-realm.properties</code>.</p>  <p>What is going on? I just want to have ActiveMQ authentication function appropriately.</p>  <p>The salient part of <code>login.config</code> looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>activemq {     org.apache.activemq.jaas.PropertiesLoginModule required         org.apache.activemq.jaas.properties.user="users.properties"         org.apache.activemq.jaas.properties.group="groups.properties"; }; </code></pre>